title: Shit Robot "Take 'Em Up" (2010)
description: The music video for "Take 'Em Up" by Shit Robot, featuring Nancy Whang, merges retro and modern visuals to create a vibrant, psychedelic effect. Set against an electro-disco track, the video shows characters in colorful 80s outfits moving through surreal cityscapes with playful animations and dynamic edits, enhancing the song's upbeat rhythm. Rotoscoping by Magdelena Turnier, Jairo Neto, Camilo Rosas, Brett Bittner, Atsushi Yamamoto, Eoin Whelehan and Chris Mooney. Contributed by Till Brokhausen.

This collaboration is a standout part of 'The Color Purple' soundtrack, showcasing the artistic depth and vulnerability of both artists.

title: Kevin McGloughlin for Max Cooper 'Repetition' (2019)
description: 'Repetition' is an attempt to convey the importance of our endless endeavours toward human development and growth amidst a chaotic and disorienting landscape. The struggle for a fruitful future is challenging with the distractions of everyday life alongside its ever-growing technological 'advancements'. The hope is for humanity to strive through all of this in a meaningful and positive way.

The struggle for a fruitful future is challenging with the distractions of everyday life alongside its ever-growing technological 'advancements'. The hope is for humanity to strive through all of this in a meaningful and positive way.
